# MandarinOS Scorecard & Challenge Mode Spec (v2)

## 1. Purpose

Define a clear, credible, and interpretable system for:
- Tracking conversation behaviour
- Presenting session-level performance
- Saving benchmark sessions (Challenge Mode)

This system measures conversation capability, not vocabulary knowledge.

---

## 2. Core Principles

### 2.1 Always Track, Selectively Show
- Tracking: always on (background)
- Scoring: shown only at end of session

### 2.2 Single Scoring Engine
All modes use:
- same metrics
- same thresholds
- same labels

No variation between Normal and Challenge Mode scoring.

### 2.3 No Live Scoring
- No metrics shown during conversation
- All feedback is post-session only

---

## 3. Modes

### 3.1 Normal Mode

- Tracking: enabled
- Scorecard: shown at end
- Persistence: NOT saved by default

Purpose:
Low-pressure practice

---

### 3.2 Challenge Mode

- Tracking: enabled
- Scorecard: shown at end
- Persistence: saved to history

Additional behaviour:
- conversation tracker hidden
- hints only shown when clicked

Purpose:
Benchmark performance

---

### 3.3 Design Rule

Challenge Mode is a measurement mode, not a different scoring system.

---

## 4. Session Object

Each session generates:

{
  session_id,
  mode,  // normal | challenge
  timestamp,
  total_turns,
  recovery_uses,
  successful_recoveries,
  suggestion_clicks,
  card_opens,
  support_uses,
  questions_asked,
  depth_responses,
  unmatched_responses,
  engines_used
}

---

## 5. Metrics & Threshold Logic

### 5.1 Conversation Flow

Raw: total_turns

0–5 → Short  
6–10 → Holding  
11–18 → Sustained  
19+ → Natural  

---

### 5.2 Recovery Ability

Raw:
- recovery_uses
- successful_recoveries

Derived:
recovery_success_rate = successful_recoveries / recovery_uses

0 recoveries → Smooth  
1–3 + ≥70% success → Recovered smoothly  
4–7 + ≥50% success → Recovered with effort  
8+ OR <50% success → Struggling to recover  

---

### 5.3 Support Level

Raw:
support_uses = suggestion_clicks + card_opens

Derived:
support_per_turn = support_uses / total_turns

0–0.15 → Independent  
0.16–0.40 → Lightly supported  
0.41–0.80 → Assisted  
0.81+ → Heavily guided  

---

### 5.4 Participation

Raw: questions_asked

0 → Responding only  
1–2 → Occasional questions  
3–5 → Active participant  
6+ → Leading the conversation  

---

### 5.5 Expression Depth

Raw: depth_responses

Triggered by markers:
因为, 所以, 觉得, 但是, 其实, 对我来说

0 → Basic answers  
1–2 → Some extension  
3–5 → Explaining ideas  
6+ → Expressive speaker  

---

### 5.6 Stability

Raw: unmatched_responses

Derived:
unmatched_rate = unmatched_responses / total_turns

0–0.10 → Stable  
0.11–0.25 → Some friction  
0.26–0.45 → Unstable  
0.46+ → Breaking down  

---

## 6. Scorecard Display

Format:

Number → Label → Meaning

Example:

14 turns → Sustained  
5 recoveries (4 successful) → Recovered with effort  
7 support uses → Assisted  
3 questions → Active participant  
4 extended responses → Explaining ideas  
2 unmatched → Some friction  

---

## 7. Session Behaviour

During conversation:
- No scoring shown

End of session:
- Scorecard always shown

---

## 8. Persistence Rules

Normal Mode:
- Not saved by default

Challenge Mode:
- Saved to history

Future:
- Optional "Save this session" for Normal Mode

---

## 9. Progress View (Deferred – Not Phase 1)

Rationale:
- Avoid premature complexity
- Validate scoring first

Current Design:
- Only Challenge Mode sessions saved

Future Scope:
- Show last 5–10 sessions
- Focus on:
  - turns
  - support level
  - participation

Example:

Day 1: 6 turns | heavily guided | 0 questions  
Day 5: 14 turns | assisted | 3 questions  
Day 10: 22 turns | mostly independent | 6 questions  

Principle:
Progress shows direction, not scores

---

## 10. Summary

- Always track behaviour
- Show scorecard after each session
- Save only Challenge Mode sessions
- Use one consistent scoring system
- Progress view deferred